The paper discusses the correlation-immune functions in cryptography, which falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of Fourier spectral characterizations, which is a topic in "Information Theory" (cs.IT) and "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper proposes new methods for characterizing Boolean functions, which could be relevant to "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS).
